ce:section.ce:para:
The morphologies of the prepared dried complexes were examined using SEM (Fig. 9
                           ) and TEM (Fig. 10
                           ). The SEM images of polyelectrolyte complexes (Fig. 9) indicate the formation of compact compatible structure, with a rough irregular surface, resulting from the molecular ionic interaction between their carboxylate groups of CMC, GQDs and protonated amino and imine groups Cs derivatives. The formation of rough patches may be attributed to the formation of aggregates of GQDs in the polyelectrolyte complexes.
